tourBios.carHigh: 2013: Made three cuts in eight starts on PGA TOUR Canada, including a T5 finish at the Dakota Dunes Open.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Won four events in two years at Central Oklahoma...Was the 2012 NCAA Division II national champion, Arnold Palmer Award recipient and was on the All-America and All-Nicklaus teams...Member of four state championship teams in high school.
tourBios.personal: Lists "being on the 18th green and competing" as his biggest thrill in golf...Favorite courses played are Castle Pines, Colorado GC, Boone Valley GC, PGA National GC and Wildfire GC...Course he'd most like to play is Augusta National...Keeps brother's dog tags as lucky charms...Favorite college team is the North Carolina Tar Heels. Favorite pro teams are the Oklahoma City Thunder and the Green Bay Packers...Favorite TV show is "The Big Bang Theory."...Favorite movies are "Happy Gilmore," "8 Seconds" and "Shooter." ...Favorite artists are Toby Keith and Bone-Thugs N' Harmony...Favorite book is The 8 Traits of Champion Golfers...Favorite food is chicken fingers and ribs...Favorite athletes to watch are Tiger Woods and Kevin Durant...Keeps beef jerky and Clif bars in bag as snacks...Dream foursome would include his dad, Jordan and Arnold Palmer...Favorite quote is, "If you've never made a mistake, you've never tried something new."

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the PGA TOUR Canada was T5th in 2013 at the Dakota Dunes Open presented by SASKTEL.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks 81st in Scoring Average (Actual) on the PGA TOUR Canada.
